The paper is about image captioning, which is a task related to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also proposes a new metric for measuring the diversity of image captions, which involves latent semantic analysis and kernelization, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the tradeoff between diversity and accuracy in captioning models, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR).
